	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65300989"><p>
UBI or similar schemes, while having populist appeal, misunderstand the nature of money.  There is no such thing as "free money" from the government - it was either taken from someone else (via taxes, etc...), or was printed (creating inflation, and the attendant macro effects.)
</p><p>
UBI schemes, because they are paid by taxpayer dollars, are always a zero sum game.  Society as a whole is never made better.  Unlike free trade, in which both parties benefit from a transaction, in UBI schemes, there are only hos<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

